cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on the performance of edge content caching for mobile video streaming, which involves wireless networks and multimedia content delivery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also analyzes the request patterns and user behaviors in mobile video streaming, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of caching solutions, which could be considered as a security issue and thus falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves experiments and analysis, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
